The paper deals with the geometric problem of reconstructing the order type of a set of points in the plane from their radial system. This problem is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of convex hulls, which is a common technique in computational geometry and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the number of possible order types that can be obtained from a given radial system, which is a topic in graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GT).
